Diabetic Jedi 2025. 2. 21. 오전 4:39
When I worked at Best Buy we had a theory that if we wanted to buy certain things, like cameras, that were super expensive we would buy it and return it after a week so that it gets marked as open box. The reason is that each product has a pricing matrix where the longer it is around the more of a discount it got but it usually only happened when a manager was trying to clear out older stock. Cameras could be marked down to 50% off after about 10 weeks. Because of that my wife was able to get a $1000 SLR for $500 CAD (this was 2005).

Dubz 2025. 2. 21. 오전 8:51

JaminCollins 2025. 2. 21. 오후 11:29
the problem you are going to have, is any temp over ~150c will result in nozzle ooze which will throw off your probing. You don't want to delete the existing you want to add another config file that is included at the end of printer.cfg but before the #*# comment block. Then in that file, place your updated version of the macro. Since it appears last (due to load order) it will overwrite the previous implementation.

JaminCollins 2025. 2. 22. 오전 4:39
Yes, we removed the custom bed_mesh.py that my improvements installed. This was the first of the three commands. Then we removed the record of bed_mesh.py being modified. This was the second command. Then we refreshed the filesystem so it would show the original file. This was the third command.

JaminCollins 2025. 2. 22. 오전 4:41
the K2 uses an overlay filesystem. The firmware files are written on what is normally seen as a read only storage. There is a 200 meg storage that tracks changes made to any file that is then overlaid on top of that read only filesystem.

gennro 2025. 2. 22. 오전 9:31
It's due to in the US we use split phase 120v at 60hz, our houses typically have two 120v split phase lines coming in with a neutral. Newer houses probably built in the past 30 years or so are wired properly where older houses may have some issues causing weird crap.
오전 9:33
So if you are having dimming flickering issues at your house its due to crappy wiring, probably doesn't have grounds, or no netural ground bond in your main breaker panel or something else, it's hard to say.
오전 9:34
could be power company as well.
오전 9:36
Electrical codes wasn't a much of a thing prior to like 1980 in residential applications for sure.

JaminCollins
the problem you are going to have, is any temp over ~150c will result in nozzle ooze which will throw off your probing. You don't want to delete the existing you want to add another config file that is included at the end of printer.cfg but before the #*# comment block. Then in that file, place your updated version of the macro. Since it appears last (due to load order) it will overwrite the previous implementation.

raffirmna 2025. 2. 23. 오전 5:48
Anyway dont under-evaluate the fumes and particulate from printing ABS/ASA and others. I have been POISONED by ABS printing some month ago. Really bad experience... I felt like dyiing for not capable to breath anymore. After 24h all was fine again, but from that moment I started digging in air filtrations, air purifiers and so on... dont trust the little tiny carbon filters in the K2 Plus, they filter out less then 20% of the VOCs, you need FULL carbon layer and also an HEPA filter for 2.5 particulate. I'm currently testing some filtering solution for the K2 with a professional air quality monitor, both on the exaust fans and an insider, recirculating, system (best one if you print with hot chamber) but I have to still make some tests before the design release
Patrokle
Mine also arrived today, ordered on 10.02 (Germany)
